Eskom says the rotational load shedding is likely to last until 11pm tonight. JOHANNESBURG – Eskom has announced that rotational load shedding has moved up to stage 3 from 10:00am. The power utility said it’s due to the loss of additional power station units, which includes a reduction in imports from Mozambique. The rotational load shedding is likely to last until 11pm tonight. The utility's Andrew Etzinger said, “It’s been necessary to escalate from stage 2 to stage 3 because of a number of failures that occurred over the last two days.” 